BLUETONGUE - EUROPE (10): ITALY (SICILIA) OVINE, SEROTYPE 3, NEW STRAIN, OIE, REQUEST FOR INFORMATION
*****************************************************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Mon 4 Dec 2017
Source: OIE, WAHID [edited] http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=25341


Bluetongue [BTV], Italy
-----------------------
Information received on 4 Dec 2017 from Dr Silvio Borrello, Chief Veterinary Officer, Food Safety and Collegial Bodies for Health Protection, Ministere de la Sante, Department for Veterinary Public Health, Rome, Italy

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 26 Oct 2017
Date of confirmation of the event: 24 Nov 2017
Reason for notification: new strain of a listed disease
Causal agent: Bluetongue virus
Serotype: 3
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (basic)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1 (BTV3_2017_1): Trapani, Sicilia
Date of start of the outbreak: 26 Oct 2017
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Sheep / 443 / 40 / 1 / - / -

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed in percentages]:
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Sheep / 9.03 / 0.23 / 2.50 / **
* Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter
** Not calculated because of missing information

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: vectors

Control measures
Measures applied: movement control inside the country; screening; zoning; vaccination permitted (if a vaccine exists); no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type:
Experimental Zooprophylactic Institute (IZSAM), Teramo (national laboratory)
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Sheep / seroneutralization test (SNT) / 24 Nov 2017 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[A new BTV-3 outbreak started in Tunisia on 1 Nov 2016, reported to the OIE at the end of December 2016 as "a new strain" (see 20161230.4731667). It will be interesting to obtain information on the genotyping results of the Tunisian and the current Sicilian isolates and to investigate possible connections between the 2 events. BTV-3 is considered to be the 1st BT strain detected outside southern Africa, namely in Cyprus in 1943, when its high pathogenicity in sheep was reported. The collection of BTV-3 isolates at the Pirbright BT reference laboratory includes strains from Cyprus (1958) as well as USA, Zimbabwe, Trinidad/St Andrews, Australia and Nigeria; see the web-page "ReoID - Phylogenetic sequence analysis and improved diagnostic assay systems for viruses of the family Reoviridae," at http://www.reoviridae.org/dsRNA_virus_proteins/ReoID/btv-3.htm. - Mod.AS

HealthMap/ProMED-mail map:
Sicily, Italy: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5482645,13616]
